							<p>Ultimately, almost everything has a happy ending – the Atlas contained copies of maps with borders decided upon in the Treaty of Versailles. But scattered throughout, there are question marks and hopes of vindication (the plebiscite in Silesia, the broken Polish-Czech border at Spisz and Orawy. The final triumph is the recovery of… a mess.</p>
